    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Defense Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of War</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MJJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCloy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SHL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-27">27 November
                            1943.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10065 (To <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">Stimson</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJJ1">McCloy</persName>)</p>
                <p>Have had talks with Joint Chiefs and British on civil affairs matters and
                    discussions with others including President, <persName corresp="#p_WJG1"
                        >Winant</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d336fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_351">pp. 351</ref>, <ref target="#pg_415">415</ref>, and
                        telegram printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Feel that if British
                    confirm agreement outlined in my 10064 we have accomplished all that we have set
                    out to do on civil affairs matter. <pb facs="0546" n="444" xml:id="pg_444"/>
                    Though I have only been on fringe of strategical discussions, it is clear that
                    all decisions of important matters are held up pending results Eastern
                        conference<note n="2" xml:id="d336fn2">Conference at Tehran.</note> to which
                    I did not go though I was requested to stay on here pending their return.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
